  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/multiprocessing/pool.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec covers: multiprocessing.pool.Pool — __name__=='Pool' (len=4); __module__=='multiprocessing.pool' (len=20); __doc__.__len__()==73. Pool.apply — __qualname__=='Pool.apply' (len=10); co_argcount==4; co_varnames.__len__()==4; __doc__.__len__()==60. Pool.map — __qualname__=='Pool.map' (len=8); co_argcount==4; co_varnames.__len__()==4; __doc__.__len__()==96. Pool.starmap — __qualname__=='Pool.starmap' (len=12); co_argcount==4; co_varnames.__len__()==4; __doc__.__len__()==172. Pool.apply_async — __qualname__=='Pool.apply_async' (len=16); co_argcount==6; co_varnames.__len__()==7; __doc__.__len__()==43. Pool.map_async — __qualname__=='Pool.map_async' (len=14); co_argcount==6; co_varnames.__len__()==6; __doc__.__len__()==41. Pool.close — __qualname__=='Pool.close' (len=10); co_argcount==1; co_varnames.__len__()==1; __doc__==None. Pool.terminate — __qualname__=='Pool.terminate' (len=14); co_argcount==1; __doc__==None. Pool.join — __qualname__=='Pool.join' (len=9); co_argcount==1; co_varnames.__len__()==2; __doc__==None. All verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "Pool.apply_async has the longest qualname (len=16) among async methods. Pool.map is the shortest qualname (len=8). apply and close both have qualname len==10; map_async and terminate both have len==14. close, terminate, and join all have co_argcount==1 and no docstring (__doc__==None). apply_async has the largest co_argcount (6) and the most varnames (7). Pool.starmap has the longest docstring (len=172) of the synchronous methods. All verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
